Write a C program to print the reverse of a given String 

Input as :

Enter a String : NareshIT

Output as : 

The reverse of the String is : TIhseraN

Answer:

#include<stdio.h>
int main() 
{
    char s[20];
    int i,c=0;
        printf("Enter a String:");
        scanf("%s",s);
            for(i=0;s[i]!='\0';i++)
                c++;
             while(c)
              printf("%c",s[--c]);
    
return 0;    
}
